    The ICommand for putting the latest versions of multiple Items into a set.

    If any of the Items does not exist in the set, it is added. If any of the Items already exists in the set, the version of the Item in the set is updated to the latest version. If the latest version of an Item already exists in the set, the set is not changed.

    Leasing:

    • An active lease must exist on the Item that owns the set to which the Items are being added.
    • Active leases must exist on the Items being added to the set.
    Authorization:
    • The current user must have the SecurityAccessLevel.UPDATE access level for the Item that owns the set.
    • The current user must have at least the SecurityAccessLevel.READ_CLOAKED access level, or the SecurityGrantLevel.UPDATE grant level, for the Items being added to the set.
    Validation:
    • The Item that owns the set must not already be marked as deleted.
    • The Items being added to the set may already be marked as deleted.
    • The Item that owns the set must not have been the source in a merge operation.
    • The Items being added to the set must not have been sources in merge operations.
    • The Item that owns the set must not have ProhibitedEdit associated with its ItemType.
    • The Items being added to the set must not have ProhibitedEdit associated with their ItemTypes.
    • The return value of getSetItemIdentifier() must correspond to an Entity.
    • If a Link is being added to the set, its ends must also be in the set.
    • It is not possible to add an Item to the set that it owns.
    • It is not possible to add Items to a set in the same CommandList as a MergeEntities command.
